Modify the way the knowledge base is embedded in libgpr2

Using the incbin directive in an assembly file was breaking the traceability
between the actual gprconfig knowledge base data and libgpr2. The new
mechanism makes sure that upon update, the new kb data is properly embedded
in the library.

Fixes eng/gpr/gpr-issues#250

Modify the way the knowledge base is embedded in libgpr2

The embedded KB is now generated as Ada source, allowing simplification
in the KB parser to retrieve it, and proper traceability in gprbuild to
ensure it's updated when needed.

Fixes eng/gpr/gpr-issues#250

doc: Use sphinx embedded search for offline usage

Pagefind does not work if the documentation HTML files are not hosted
by a web server (local, or not).

To ensure that the user can always have a search engine available, the
default sphinx search engine is used when the detected protocol is
neither `http` nor `https`.

To do so, the inherited RTD search template is extended with the
pagefind code. Both search engines have their own result `<div>`, so we
can display the correct one.

Co-Author: Boris Yakobowski <yakobowski@adacore.com>
Issue: eng/gpr/gpr-issues#260

gpr2-kb: fix Parse_All_Dirs behavior for <directory> node with group 0

The <directory> node of <compiler_description> allows to compute a value
from a list of directories and files. If the field "group" is set to its
default value 0, then, according to the documentation, the value parsed
in the regex of <directory> shall be returned.

This was not the case until now. This commit fixes this feature.

Issue: eng/gpr/gpr-issues#155

gpr2-kb: fix Parse_All_Dirs last path character computation

In the previous implementation, `Last` index was pointing to:
- the first directory separator encountered, or
- the character AFTER the last character of the path

In the second case, exceptions were raised during the regex checking.

This commit implements `Last` as the last character before a directory
separator or as the last character of the path.
